President Donald Trump spoke with King Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud of Saudi Arabia. They praised the resilience of the communities affected by Hurricane Harvey and expressed condolences to the families who lost loved ones. They discussed the need to defeat terrorism, cut off terrorist funding, and combat extremist ideology. President Trump urged all parties involved in the Qatar dispute to find a diplomatic resolution that maintains unity while fighting terrorism, in line with commitments made at the Riyadh Summit. They also discussed the threat posed by Iran to the region.